Package: ComputationalValidity
Type: Package
Title: This pacakge implements simulations to illustrate how validity can be
  assessed when there are formal models describing the processes underlying 
  behavioral performance.
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Gidon T. Frischkorn
Maintainer: Gidon T. Frischkorn <gidon.frischkorn@psychologie.uzh.ch>
Description: Implements parameter recovery simulations to assess the validity of
    behavioral indicators for measuring cognitive processes. Uses the Diffusion
    Model for Conflict tasks (DMC) and the Shrinking Spotlight model (SSP) to
    demonstrate how generative cognitive models enable validity assessment through
    parameter recovery analysis. Accompanies Frischkorn, Rebmann, & Oberauer
    (submitted) "Validity is a Theoretical Problem."
